rmvbc@yahoo.com                                                      ', N'2404601719          ', N'2404601719          ', 1500, 56, 1000, 320, 200, 100, 200, 3376, 350, 8, 2800, 0, -576, N'Jennifer Reap                                                                   ', N'PAYMENT
- $350
- Payable by credit card or check
- Payment must be received by the Age Group Coordinator by the late registrationdate

VENUE DETAILS
- Location:  Covenant Life Church, 7501 Muncaster Mill Road, Gaithersburg, MD 20877
- No food table set ups are allowed in the venue
- ONLY WAER is allowed in the gyms - all other food must be kept in the adjoining lobbies
- All teams are responsible for ensuring their campsite and surrounding areas are left CLEAN and free of all trash
- Campsite are located in the adjoining lobbies
- NO campsites are allowed in the gyms
- Minimal bleacher seating is available
- NO personal chairs may be brought into the gyms, with the exception of the Event Cetner, where personal chairs may be on the carpeted STAGE AREA only
- Tri-pods and other photography equipment must be kept off the playing surface

FORMAT
- Start time:  8:00am
- The first matches of the day will begin at 8:00am.  ALL following matches are labeled ASAP and are approximate, with the second matches beginning 15 minutes after the end of the first, and all subsequent matches beginning 10 minutes after the completion of the preceding match.
- Pool Play: two sets to 21 (starting at 4)***
- Playoffs:  Match Play (best 2 out of 3 sets to 25, 3rd to 15)
- All teams into playoffs:  Gold/Silver
- Medals are awarded to 1st and 2nd place in the GOLD bracket only
***Format may be adjusted if there are less than 8 teams participating

WORK TEAMS
- Each team is required to provide a certified referee (R1) for one match during the day in addition to the regular work team (scorekeeper, 2 lines persons, Rs, libero tracker, score flipper)
- The Chesapeake Region requires a USAV registered, rostered, and background checked adult member to be courtside for all Junior work teams

ROSTER REQUIREMENTS
- Please send a team representative to check-in with the tournament director immediately upon arrival
- You MUST have a valid USAV logoed, Sports Engine roster to participate in this event (MUST contain USAV logo in the upper right hand corner)
- All teams are required to update and verify your official Sports Engine roster at this time, noting any absences 
- ONLY jersey numbers may be handwritten on the roster
- Proof of a player''s age should be available upon request

CONCESSIONS
- Concessions will be available for purchase on site
- Food nearby:  Starbucks, Giant Food, McDonalds, Wing Stop, Ledo''s, Subway, Dunkin Donuts, Pap John''s, Taco Bell, Wendy''s, Checkers, etc


Tournament Directors:
- Jennifer Reap, Club Director
- Sarah Kenneweg, Asst. Club Director
- Matthew Smith, Tournament Coordinator
- Additional Platform VBC staff as available
